# Amplitude Experiment: Experimentation Platform

## Product Overview

Amplitude Experiment is a comprehensive platform for designing, executing, and analyzing controlled experiments (A/B tests and Multi-Armed Bandits) to drive data-driven product decisions. The platform enables product teams to test hypotheses about changes by comparing metrics between different user groups and determining the statistical significance of observed differences.

Amplitude Experiment provides robust statistical analysis tools, including Welch's T-test, experiment design capabilities with configurable parameters, sample size and duration estimation, real-time monitoring with Cumulative Exposure graphs, and support for both traditional A/B testing and more advanced Multi-Armed Bandit experiments. Users can configure Minimum Detectable Effect (MDE) settings to ensure experiments are properly powered to detect meaningful changes.

